"{\"uid\": \"thenation.com-article-society-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Forgot Your Password?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 23, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"New toThe Nation?Subscribe  Print subscriber?Activateyour online access  The Olympic Games supercharge the problems that already exist in a host city.\", \"from\": 25, \"to\": 175, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We saw that in Paris-but what will happen in LA?\", \"from\": 176, \"to\": 224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fireworks illuminate the sky at the end of the closing ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games at the Stade de France on August 12, 2024, in Paris, France.\", \"from\": 226, \"to\": 382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 368, \"end\": 373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 375, \"end\": 381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8496623484340249, \"rank\": 0.1769381020189023, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris-At the closing ceremony of the Paris Olympics, outgoing International Olympic Committee President Thomas Bachsaidthat the 2024 Summer Games \\\"were sensational Olympic Games from start to finish.\\\"\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He then added, \\\"Or dare I say: Seine-sational Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bach's cringeworthy pun was only outmatched by the hyperbole of the Olympic faithful proclaiming Paris to be \\\"the best Olympics ever.\\\"\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.130196016791234e-23, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 736, \"end\": 741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In reality, amid the inspiring, often poetic, feats of athleticism, these Games magnified the social problems of Paris-and the world.\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 907, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympians make the Olympics, and Paris 2024 was no exception.\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 942, \"end\": 952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8070402024700522e-35, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Games featured athletes who brought exquisite skill and joy to the competition, but they also brought their politics.\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It started with the opening ceremony, when members of the Algerian teamreleasedroses into the Seine to honor those who were shot and drowned in the river by French police in 1961, the final year of Algeria's war of independence from colonial France.\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1157, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998524344955, \"rank\": 1.4755898712804074e-07, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 1193, \"end\": 1198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2792265924553556e-18, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1256, \"end\": 1269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1085540163067506e-66, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1297, \"end\": 1304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999936344466, \"rank\": 6.365373769726863e-09, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 1332, \"end\": 1347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_colonial_empire\", \"score\": 0.9999949333470002, \"rank\": 5.066679095287995e-06, \"text\": \"colonial France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_colonial_empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_colonial_empire\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Upwards of 120 people were killed in an incident that, for decades, French officials attempted tocover up.Fa\\u00efza Zerouala, a French journalist of Algerian descent who writes forMediapart, told us, \\\"I was very proud they did that.\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1417, \"end\": 1423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9829917226872886, \"rank\": 0.011442742948012025, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1473, \"end\": 1479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9829917226872886, \"rank\": 0.011442742948012025, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1494, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998524344955, \"rank\": 1.4755898712804074e-07, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For me, it was proof that Algerian descendants still know who they are\\\" and that \\\"we do not forget the past,\\\" even if many in France are \\\"blind to its colonial background.\\\"\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1604, \"end\": 1612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998524344955, \"rank\": 1.4755898712804074e-07, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 1704, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8496623484340249, \"rank\": 0.1769381020189023, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She added, \\\"It was a very important tribute to the martyrs.\\\"\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Later in the opening-ceremony procession, one of Palestine's flag bearers, boxer Waseem Abu Sal, wore a white shirtembroideredwith depictions of Israeli fighter jets bombing children in Gaza.\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1862, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.999522069829013, \"rank\": 0.00047815869703645927, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}, {\"begin\": 1894, \"end\": 1900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Waseem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasim\"}, {\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shorea_robusta\", \"score\": 0.9998470129406719, \"rank\": 0.0001527708425835427, \"text\": \"Sal\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shorea_robusta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shorea_robusta\"}, {\"begin\": 1958, \"end\": 1965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999999153842545, \"rank\": 8.459391658089167e-08, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 1999, \"end\": 2003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9999393999942032, \"rank\": 6.060367816527335e-05, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was one of eight Palestinians competing in Paris, including Layla Al-Masri whoseta Palestinian national record in the 800-meter run.\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2140, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2025, \"end\": 2037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999999991978257, \"rank\": 8.013655987974912e-10, \"text\": \"Palestinians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 2051, \"end\": 2056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2068, \"end\": 2073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Layla_Miller\", \"score\": 0.743478662821316, \"rank\": 0.3450285125456026, \"text\": \"Layla\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Layla_Miller\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Layla_Miller\"}, {\"begin\": 2091, \"end\": 2102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999999950805432, \"rank\": 4.8839441900260296e-09, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans in Paris celebrated Palestinian athletes wherever they went-even as the press largely ignored them.\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2149, \"end\": 2154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2166, \"end\": 2177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999999950805432, \"rank\": 4.8839441900260296e-09, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Few journalists bothered to interview members of the Palestinian Olympic team.\", \"from\": 2246, \"to\": 2324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2299, \"end\": 2310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999999950805432, \"rank\": 4.8839441900260296e-09, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The overall absence of attention Palestinian athletes received-the erasure of their struggles-mirrored the war on Gaza and the attendant suffering of deliberately unheard Palestinian civilians.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2358, \"end\": 2369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999999950805432, \"rank\": 4.8839441900260296e-09, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 2439, \"end\": 2443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9999393999942032, \"rank\": 6.060367816527335e-05, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 2496, \"end\": 2507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999999950805432, \"rank\": 4.8839441900260296e-09, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition brought-also underreported-political statements to the playing field.\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When Manizha Talash, a breakdancer from Afghanistan representing theRefugee Olympic Team, finished her performance, sheunveileda cape reading \\\"Free Afghan Women.\\\"\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2611, \"end\": 2618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manizha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Manizha\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manizha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manizha\"}, {\"begin\": 2619, \"end\": 2625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Talash_(1969_film)\", \"score\": 0.858682698055531, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Talash\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Talash_(1969_film)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Talash_(1969_film)\"}, {\"begin\": 2646, \"end\": 2657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999998735802, \"rank\": 1.2650082457458526e-10, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While fans in attendance applauded, as did the athlete from the Netherlands against whom Talash was competing, the Olympic powerbrokers disqualified her.\", \"from\": 2769, \"to\": 2922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2833, \"end\": 2844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999999992169251, \"rank\": 7.826357150688754e-10, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, they disqualified someonefrom the refugee teamfor raising awareness aboutwhy she is a refugee.\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 3022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By disqualifying Talash, Olympic honchos essentially did the bidding of the Taliban, whose prohibition on women playing sports is precisely why she could not compete under the flag of her home country.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3099, \"end\": 3106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"score\": 0.9984587159873802, \"rank\": 0.0015436632359834394, \"text\": \"Taliban\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zerouala also pointed to the importance of Kaylia Nemour, one of France's top gymnasts, who chose to switch nationalities and compete for Algeria after a protracteddisputewith the French gymnastics federation, which was inflexible about where the 17-year-old gymnast trained.\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3291, \"end\": 3297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8496623484340249, \"rank\": 0.1769381020189023, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3364, \"end\": 3371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999936344466, \"rank\": 6.365373769726863e-09, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 3406, \"end\": 3434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French gymnastics federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Gymnastics_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zerouala dubbed Nemour's gold-medal win on the uneven bars \\\"a colonial reparation.\\\"\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3585, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The victory made Nemour the first African athlete to win a medal in Olympic gymnastics.\", \"from\": 3586, \"to\": 3673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While there was no shortage of coverage of women's boxing gold medalist Imane Khelif, who triumphed despite facing downbigotryand lies about her sex and gender, less was made about her winning gold in Franceas an Algerian.Khelif's refusal to speak French in her last press conference, opting for Arabic and English instead, revealed a politics of resistance that Western journalists did not understand.\", \"from\": 3675, \"to\": 4077, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3747, \"end\": 3759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 4038, \"end\": 4045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.3355073897093706e-12, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Politicians often try to exploit the Olympics-and Olympic athletes-for their political careers.\", \"from\": 4079, \"to\": 4174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But this backfired for French President Emmanuel Macron, whose constant, unrequested hugging of any French Olympian within his five-meter radius was off-putting.\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4198, \"end\": 4214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 4215, \"end\": 4230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 4275, \"end\": 4281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9829917226872886, \"rank\": 0.011442742948012025, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4282, \"end\": 4290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.198512800494501e-16, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After French judoka Romane Dicko won bronze, Macron cupped her head in his hands, an experience that, she said, made her feel \\\"a little embarrassed.\\\"\", \"from\": 4337, \"to\": 4486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4343, \"end\": 4349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9829917226872886, \"rank\": 0.011442742948012025, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4382, \"end\": 4388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.978261874105083e-38, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French Olympian Hugo Hay, who qualified for the final in the 5000 meters, even called out Macron for his brazen politicking,declaring, \\\"These are not his Games, but those of the athletes.\\\"\", \"from\": 4487, \"to\": 4675, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4487, \"end\": 4493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9829917226872886, \"rank\": 0.011442742948012025, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4577, \"end\": 4583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.978261874105083e-38, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Macron's tanned visage also evinced a cacophony of jeers when it appeared on the jumbotron at the Olympic fan zone in Place de la Bataille Stalingrad during the gold-medal men's basketball game between the United States and France.\", \"from\": 4677, \"to\": 4908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4677, \"end\": 4683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.978261874105083e-38, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 4883, \"end\": 4896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.5995581548213766, \"rank\": 0.6678949188811621, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4901, \"end\": 4907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8496623484340249, \"rank\": 0.1769381020189023, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the Games did not boost his popularity: In early Augustonly 27 percentof the country had confidence in his ability to address France's problems, only two points higher than in early July.\", \"from\": 4909, \"to\": 5100, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5039, \"end\": 5045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8496623484340249, \"rank\": 0.1769381020189023, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amid the media hullabaloo over the Paris Olympics, serious social issues in Paris remain unresolved.\", \"from\": 5102, \"to\": 5202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5178, \"end\": 5183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To police the Olympics, there were heavily armed security forces from more than 30 different countries, but that is not all.\", \"from\": 5203, \"to\": 5327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France's political leaders also transformed the city into their ownpanopticon, with the French National Assembly greenlighting the use of algorithmic video surveillance.\", \"from\": 5328, \"to\": 5497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5328, \"end\": 5334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8496623484340249, \"rank\": 0.1769381020189023, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 5416, \"end\": 5440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4546926449606446e-56, \"text\": \"French National Assembly\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Parliament\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They built this security architecture ostensibly to prevent terrorism, but as is often the case, it was wielded against activists.\", \"from\": 5498, \"to\": 5628, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(There were also heavily armed police units patrolling working-class, immigrant neighborhoods far from the Olympic zone.)\", \"from\": 5629, \"to\": 5750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, we interviewed Noah Farjon, an activist from the counter-Olympics organizationSaccage 2024who was arrested not once but twice, simply for trying to organize informational tours for visiting journalists and concerned locals interested to learn more about the social and environmental effects of the Olympics on Saint Denis, an area to the north of Paris thatexperiencedintensified gentrification because of the Games.\", \"from\": 5752, \"to\": 6178, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5755, \"end\": 5760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5777, \"end\": 5781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\", \"score\": 0.9999999924630174, \"rank\": 7.535045946163497e-09, \"text\": \"Noah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\"}, {\"begin\": 6078, \"end\": 6083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999990741148134, \"rank\": 9.028692669811809e-07, \"text\": \"Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6109, \"end\": 6114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These \\\"Toxic Tours,\\\" as Saccage 2024 called them, nabbed the attention of security officials who arrested Farjon and two journalists, detaining them for 10 hours.\", \"from\": 6179, \"to\": 6341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Days later, Farjon was placed in custodyagainand fined 135 euros for organizing what police described as an illegal demonstration.\", \"from\": 6342, \"to\": 6472, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After his second arrest, Farjon told us that this \\\"gross police overreach\\\"-approximately 60 police were on hand-\\\"proved their point\\\" about the intensified surveillance of political speech during the Games.\", \"from\": 6473, \"to\": 6678, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Police officers pointed to his previous arrest, when charges were dropped, to justify arresting him a second time, he said.\", \"from\": 6679, \"to\": 6802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The experience, he told us, \\\"worries me for what's to come\\\" after the Games.\", \"from\": 6803, \"to\": 6879, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Off the field, the most under-discussed story were the people in Paris who paid for the Olympics with their shelter and sense of stability.\", \"from\": 6881, \"to\": 7020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6946, \"end\": 6951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"About12,500 unhousedand precariously housed people were bused out of the city.\", \"from\": 7021, \"to\": 7099, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Making the city \\\"Olympics ready\\\" meant a \\\"social cleansing\\\"-or what activists fromLe Revers de la M\\u00e9daille(The Other Side of the Medal) callednettoyage social.\", \"from\": 7100, \"to\": 7259, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some were given shelter; others, their whereabouts are unknown.\", \"from\": 7260, \"to\": 7323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was an Olympic-size human rights travesty that deserved more coverage.\", \"from\": 7324, \"to\": 7399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, attention shifts to Los Angeles, host of the 2028 Summer Games.\", \"from\": 7401, \"to\": 7469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7426, \"end\": 7437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1053982608768021e-31, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The finale of the Paris 2024 closing ceremony involved a gaudy, star-studded handoff of the torch to LA Mayor Karen Bass.\", \"from\": 7470, \"to\": 7591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7488, \"end\": 7498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8070402024700522e-35, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 7580, \"end\": 7590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But not even the shine from Snoop Dogg's golden shoes could blind Kenneth Mejia, LA's city controller, from the grim realities that differentiate LA from Paris.\", \"from\": 7592, \"to\": 7752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7620, \"end\": 7630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 7658, \"end\": 7671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenneth_Mejia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenneth Mejia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenneth_Mejia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenneth_Mejia\"}, {\"begin\": 7746, \"end\": 7751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mejiaposteda graphic comparing the two cities on metrics like transit use and the population of unhoused people.\", \"from\": 7753, \"to\": 7865, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When we consider the massive number of unhoused and precariously housed people in LA-10 times as many as Paris, according to Mejia-one shudders what the \\\"solutions\\\" will entail, especially with California Governor Gavin Newsom waging his war against homeless encampments.\", \"from\": 7866, \"to\": 8137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7971, \"end\": 7976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 8060, \"end\": 8070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1934774947799127e-18, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}, {\"begin\": 8080, \"end\": 8092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gavin_Newsom\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.117717527305388e-76, \"text\": \"Gavin Newsom\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gavin_Newsom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gavin_Newsom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics are an inequality machine, supercharging all the problems that already exist in the host city.\", \"from\": 8139, \"to\": 8246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles brings Hollywood glitz and glamor but also homelessness, displacement, racialized policing, and a changing environment.\", \"from\": 8247, \"to\": 8378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8247, \"end\": 8258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1053982608768021e-31, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 8266, \"end\": 8275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.647182523084445e-22, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If there is one lesson to learn from Paris it is this: Be sober-minded about hosting the Games, do not drink the Kool-Aid, and definitely do not wait until 2027 to start organizing.\", \"from\": 8379, \"to\": 8560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8416, \"end\": 8421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.881787752853673e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are already activists fromNOlympicsLAdoing grassroots activism.\", \"from\": 8561, \"to\": 8630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"People should join their efforts to make sure that the most marginalized populations do not pay the highest price for the next Games.\", \"from\": 8631, \"to\": 8764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even before February 28, the reasons for Donald Trump's imploding approval rating were abundantly clear: untrammeled corruption and personal enrichment to the tune of billions of dollars during an affordability crisis, a foreign policy guided only by his own derelict sense of morality, and the deployment of a murderous campaign of occupation, detention, and deportation on American streets.\", \"from\": 8766, \"to\": 9158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8807, \"end\": 8819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 9.868589045411234e-12, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 9141, \"end\": 9149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.087742833661092e-18, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now an undeclared, unauthorized, unpopular, and unconstitutional war of aggression against Iran has spread like wildfire through the region and into Europe.\", \"from\": 9160, \"to\": 9316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9251, \"end\": 9255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999999977180778, \"rank\": 2.281855062772764e-09, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A new \\\"forever war\\\"-with an ever-increasing likelihood of American troops on the ground-may very well be upon us.\", \"from\": 9317, \"to\": 9430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9375, \"end\": 9383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.087742833661092e-18, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As we have seen over and over, this administration uses lies, misdirection, and attempts to flood the zone to justify its abuses of power at home and abroad.\", \"from\": 9432, \"to\": 9589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just as Trump, Marco Rubio, and Pete Hegseth offer erratic and contradictory rationales for the attacks on Iran, the administration is also spreading the lie that the upcoming midterm elections are under threat from noncitizens on voter rolls.\", \"from\": 9590, \"to\": 9833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9598, \"end\": 9603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999993115125, \"rank\": 6.883042609710611e-10, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 9605, \"end\": 9616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Rubio\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2405911666457785e-36, \"text\": \"Marco Rubio\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Rubio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Rubio\"}, {\"begin\": 9622, \"end\": 9634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pete_Hegseth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pete Hegseth\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pete_Hegseth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pete_Hegseth\"}, {\"begin\": 9697, \"end\": 9701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999999977180778, \"rank\": 2.281855062772764e-09, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When these lies go unchecked, they become the basis for further authoritarian encroachment and war.\", \"from\": 9834, \"to\": 9933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In these dark times, independent journalism is uniquely able to uncover the falsehoods that threaten our republic-and civilians around the world-and shine a bright light on the truth.\", \"from\": 9935, \"to\": 10118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Nation's experienced team of writers, editors, and fact-checkers understands the scale of what we are up against and the urgency with which we have to act.\", \"from\": 10120, \"to\": 10279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's why we are publishing critical reporting and analysis of the war on Iran, ICE violence at home, new forms of voter suppression emerging in the courts, and much more.\", \"from\": 10280, \"to\": 10452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10355, \"end\": 10359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999999977180778, \"rank\": 2.281855062772764e-09, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this journalism is possible only with your support.\", \"from\": 10454, \"to\": 10509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This March,The Nationneeds to raise $50,000 to ensure that we have the resources for reporting and analysis that sets the record straight and empowers people of conscience to organize.Will you donate today?\", \"from\": 10511, \"to\": 10717, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jules Boykoff is a professor of political science at Pacific University in Oregon and the author of six books on the Olympic Games, most recentlyWhat Are the Olympics For?\", \"from\": 10719, \"to\": 10890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10719, \"end\": 10732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jules Boykoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\"}, {\"begin\": 10772, \"end\": 10790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pacific University\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_University\"}, {\"begin\": 10794, \"end\": 10800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"score\": 0.9999987490945025, \"rank\": 1.250906610008406e-06, \"text\": \"Oregon\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dave Zirin is the sports editor atThe Nation.\", \"from\": 10892, \"to\": 10937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10892, \"end\": 10902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Zirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dave Zirin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Zirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Zirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the author of 11 books on the politics of sports.\", \"from\": 10938, \"to\": 10993, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is also the coproducer and writer of the new documentaryBehind the Shield: The Power and Politics of the NFL.\", \"from\": 10994, \"to\": 11106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11102, \"end\": 11105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9999999974779712, \"rank\": 1.426312424918927e-09, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Gaza, we watch people being starved by Israel.\", \"from\": 11108, \"to\": 11157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11111, \"end\": 11115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9999393999942032, \"rank\": 6.060367816527335e-05, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resou